hio by law  politics magazine  chambers usa reported that hill is “widely regarded as ‘one of the finest litigators in columbus on business matters’”  chambers usa recognized tom for his skills in the courtroom describing him as a “tenacious litigator”  to present fellow of the american college of trial lawyers  to present tom is one of a distinguished group of attorneys who have been listed every year in the best lawyers in america® since its inception  these accolades are the result of a number of hallmarks of tom’s practice first tom has always believed that clients come first their interests drive his work and achieving their goals in the most efficient and effective way is his “north star” to achieve the client’s goals tom stays in close contact with every client every step of the way second tom believes that powerful advocacy is the product of a thorough understanding of the facts and the law presented to a court or jury in a way that is both logically sound and pleasing in tone third tom believes that powerful advocacy is what brings about favorable settlements tom keeps a constant eye out for opportunities to resolve cases short of trial if that can be reasonably donerepresentative cases tom concentrates on the representation of business clients of all sizes including fortune  companies and nonprofit agencies in november  he obtained an  million judgment in favor of his clients against a publicly traded company arising out of a breach of merger agreement he has obtained a  million settlement on behalf of a publicly traded company against an investment banking firm for breach of fiduciary duty he successfully defended a fortune  company in a  million claim that was tried to a jury in federal court in a widelypublicized national dispute he represented donatos pizza inc in successful prosecution of trademark infringement claim involving donatos edge to edge trademark he successfully defended a pension fund in a lawsuit in federal court that had industrywide implications for the trucking industry he obtained summary judgment for mcdonald’s corporation in a race discrimination in employment case in federal court in columbus he defended the ohio state university in a lawsuit brought by the survivors of a college freshman who was killed in an elevator accident on the university campus practice areasantitrustantitrust  trade regulation litigationbanking  lendingbanking  financial institution litigationemployee relationsemployment litigationenergy  environmentenergy litigationfranchise  distributionfranchise litigationglobal businesscorporate investigationsglobal dispute litigationhealth carehealth care litigationip strategy  consultingip trademark  patent litigationlitigationantitrust  trade regulation litigationbanking  financial institution litigationclass  collective action litigationcomplex commercial litigationcorporate investigationsemployment litigationenergy litigationfranchise litigationglobal dispute litigationhealth care litigationip trademark  patent litigationpersonal injury litigationreal estate  land use litigationsecurities litigationreal estatereal estate  land use litigationreal estate services educationcornell university law school jd grinnell college ba  bar admissionsohious supreme courtus court of appeals for the sixth circuitus district court for the southern district of ohio professional affiliationsamerican bar association memberamerican college of trial lawyers national moot court competition committee national chairmanamerican inns of court duncan chapter past membercolumbus bar association membercolumbus bar foundation trustee litigation counsel of america fellowohio state bar association member special honorsselected as the  “lawyer of the year” in columbus in the area of betthecompany litigation by the best lawyers in america®recognized as a band  attorney in litigation by chambers  partners martindalehubbell rating of avselected to the ohio super lawyers listselected to the “top  ohio” and “top  