ial landlords asset purchasers trustees receivers and equipment lessors for example he has represented  lending institutions such as santander bank investors bank amboy bank sun national bank bank of oklahoma and td bank na commercial landlords such as heller industrial parks stanbery development and cheesequake commons llc his work for lenders involves workouts and asset sales including drafting forbearance andor modification agreements loan sale agreements and asset purchase agreements and defending lender liability claims including respa tila fdcpa consumer fraud and other claims state court appointed receivers in securities fraud statefederal civil rico fraudulent conveyance preferential transfer professional liability negligence and other claims representative matters clients count on mr halm to represent them in matters such as those summarized below he has served as receiver for james hankins jr the hankins group ltd hankins private client group llc and hankins life settlement llc in a multimilliondollar securities fraud case brought by the new jersey bureau of securities before the superior court of new jersey chancery division general equity part monmouth county he is responsible for winding up the affairs of the corporate defendants and locating and liquidating all assets of the defendants for distribution to the defrauded investors and creditors in this capacity he has liquidated the minimal assets left in the estate including a mansion and its contents in palm beach county florida resolved a dispute with the receivership entities’ commercial landlord and auctioned off the contents of the entities’ office located secreted assets and liquidated same and instituted legal actions resulting in the recovery of nearly  to date for the receivership estate mr halm has represented a national warehouse operator in all phases of a chapter  bankruptcy filing by a multinational tenant including but not limited to assisting the client with respect to the debtor’s rejection of the commercial lease the filing of proofs of claims including an administrative claim for postpetition damage to the client’s real property and defending the client in preferencefraudulent conveyance litigation he has represented a hedge fund in obtaining payment in full including all attorneys’ fees and costs on a loan secured by a private golf course including instituting foreclosure proceedings and obtaining the appointment of a receiver for the property and the profits generated therefrom and pursuing the client’s claim in the debtor’s subsequent chapter  bankruptcy filing by obtaining the appointment of a chapter  trustee based on the debtor’s previous fraud mr halm has represented a state chartered bank in defense of allegations that the bank violated the new jersey consumer fraud act by entering into a workout arrangement with its borrower that interfered with the borrower’s obligation to refund a membership deposit owed to a founding member of a private country club he has represented a nationally chartered bank in the foreclosure of nearly  million in crossdefaultedcrosscollateralized loans and equipment leases secured on six hotels and a catering hall including the early termination of a swap agreement and the appointment of a receiver for the property and the profits generated there from he has represented a private lending group as lead lender in resolving a defaulted loan obligation secured on a catering facility parking lot and investment properties this matter involved negotiating a forbearance and modification agreement resulting in the transfer of title by deed in lieu of foreclosure the execution of leases by the borrower for the continued use of various property and the eventual liquidation of said assets by the sale of same including the negotiation of an asset sale agreement whereby the client sold its paper and the remaining assets of the borrower to a participant in the loan leadership mr halm is active in the professional and civic communities in which he works and lives his positions include robbinsville township board of education vice president and chair of the finance facilities and transportation committee ryans quest trustee collier golf classic committee benefiting collier youth services member   turnaround management association member national association of industrial office parks member american bankruptcy institute member new jersey state bar association member robbinsville township planning board former member  robbinsville education foundation former member robert wood johnson university hospital – hamilton young professionals group former member    thomas w halm jr   seminar hill wallack llp partner thomas w halm jr to speak at national business institute seminaraugust   article nydfs cybersecurity regulations force broad range of companies nationwide to tighten their cybersecurity standardsmarch   client alert time to tighten your cybersecurity beltsmarch   infohillwallackcom attorneys resources alerts articles  publications events blogs useful links practices media news releases media mentions firm firm overview managing partner message career opportunities contact office locations princeton  roszel roadprinceton nj   morristown  washington street suite gcourthouse plazamorristown nj   yardley  township line roadsuite yardley pa   copyright  • hill wallack llp disclaimer website by firmwise recipients name enter the person or groups name to whom this page is going recipients email enter up to five email addresses separated by a comma your name enter your name for recipients to recognize and validate your email specify your email address so that recipients can respond directly message copy yourself check this if you would also like to receive a copy of this page hill thomas w  e bethany dr aurora co counselorslicensed professional  mapquest hill thomas w  e bethany dr aurora co  reviews   menu  reservations make reservations order online tickets tickets see availability nearby di